    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1652"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1652">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.67/29.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Chargé d’Affaires of Turkey</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to the Turkish Chargé d’Affaires
                    and, referring to his note of March 30, 1915, in regard to the seizure at
                    Chihuahua, Mexico, of the properties of J. E. Touche, an Ottoman Syrian, has the
                    honor to inform the Turkish Chargé d’Affaires that the Department has today
                    instructed Mr. George C. Carothers to request General Francisco Villa to order
                    the restoration to the owner of the properties mentioned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 3, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
